Sir
I haue sent this bearer for my tow whelpes
it hath pleased you to bestow vppon mee
I am intreated to meet mr High Sherriff
to morrow att Newcastle touching the bene=
volence I pray you giue mee but a touch
in a line or two what the Coontry did and
what course you did take that being all of
one hundred wee may run one and the same
coorse soe with the rembrance of my loue
to your self and my good Cosin your bed fellow
I rest
Your Kinsman and ever
Loving frend
Thomas Crompton
Stone the xiiith
of Iune 1622


To the right worrshipfulle and
my very good Cosin
Walter Bagott esquire att
Blythfeild giue these
